Abstract = {A survey was carried out on insects found in the inflorescences of
   Protea repens (L.) L. which flowers between March and July in the
   Western Cape {[}South Africa]. A total of 45 insect species was recorded
   of which 32 were Coleoptera. Chirodica spp. (Halticidae) comprised 70\%
   of all the insects found. Exclusion experiments and scanning electron
   microscope photographs show that small beetles are important vectors of
   protea pollen-a role hitherto attributed only to birds, rodents and
   large beetles.},
