Abstract = {The reproductive system of dioecious genus Leucadendron seems to be
   quite distinct from other commercial genera of the family Proteaceae.
   Controlled crosses executed between different commercial species of
   Leucadendron indicated that closely related species hybridize more
   easily than more distantly related species. When pollen was sown on an
   artifical pollen germination medium recommended for Protea no pollen
   tubes were observed. In scanning elecron microscopy observations the
